ial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 3 hours\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> Spring to Fall\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Access:<\/strong> Good parking\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82N\/2<br \/>\n<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Drive:<\/strong> From Creston, drive north on Highway 3. Turn right just before Tim Hortons on Helen Street. The parking area is on the left just as Helen St angles right.\u00a0\u00a0<\/span><\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Trail:<\/strong> Trailhead is behind the Town of Creston Public Works Yard on Helen Steet.<br \/>\nClimb steadily through a pine forest to a rock outcrop.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>References:\u00a0<\/strong><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"http:\/\/crestoncommunityforest.com\/billy-goat-bluffs\/\">http:\/\/crestoncommunityforest.com\/billy-goat-bluffs\/<\/a>.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This relatively new trail provides easy access to Arrow Mountain, known locally as Goat Mountain, from within the town of Creston.\u00a0 Views are to the west over the Creston Valley and north to Kootenay Lake. Location: North of Creston towards &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/08\/09\/billy-goat-bluffs\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_eve